 "key_findings": [
  "Within-donor E[N] split-half reproducibility is high and RISES with stimulation: Rest 0.62, Stim8h 0.68, Stim48h 0.75.",
  "Cross-donor E[N] does NOT transfer in Rest (rho=-0.11) or Stim8h (rho=-0.10), but becomes portable at Stim48h (rho=0.49).",
  "Refinement depth is therefore donor/context-specific except where the biology converges (stimulated endpoint) - consistent with cell-type-specificity of depth.",
  "Resting-sparing suppressors have LOWER E[N] at Stim48h than damaging (delta=-0.16) and generic 'other' (delta=-0.24) perturbations (kruskal p=5e-28) - a distinct refinement signature, confirming CD4 Part-2 thesis.",
  "Drug-target status is NOT enriched in any CD4 depth cluster (all OR 0.64-1.25); druggability/toxicity flat across the 9 Leiden clusters (approved/clinical 5-8%, DepMap common-essential 1-2%, LoF-intolerant 4-8%). Drug/depth co-localization is cell-context-dependent (Leiden x annotated CSV only)."
